    "body": "I also noticed the wrong rust version in my prompt \r\n```\r\nehubapps on î‚  ancser-fever-cert-support-and-refactor-ancser-asyncapi [$!?] via đź¦€ 1.68-\r\nx86_64-unknown-linux-gnu \r\n```\r\n\r\neven though rustup show looked like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nâťŻ rustup show\r\nDefault host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\nrustup home:  /home/jonas/.rustup\r\n\r\ninstalled toolchains\r\n--------------------\r\n\r\nstable-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\n1.70-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\n1.74-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\n1.75-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\n1.80-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu (default)\r\n\r\ninstalled targets for active toolchain\r\n--------------------------------------\r\n\r\narm-unknown-linux-gnueabihf\r\nx86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\n\r\nactive toolchain\r\n----------------\r\n\r\n1.80-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu (overridden by '/home/jonas/dev/ferroamp/ehubapps/rust-to\r\nolchain.toml')\r\nrustc 1.80.1 (3f5fd8dd4 2024-08-06)\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nI fixed it by removing an old override I had configured for the directory.\r\n\r\n```\r\nâťŻ cat .rustup/settings.toml\r\ndefault_toolchain = \"1.80-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\"\r\nprofile = \"default\"\r\nversion = \"12\"\r\n\r\n[overrides]\r\n\"/home/jonas/dev\" = \"1.68-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter deleting the override row it shows correctly again. It appears that starship takes the override version even though it is not installed anymore, and that the override has priority over the version set in rust-toolchain.toml even though that appears to not be the case for rustup.\r\n\r\n```\r\nehubapps on î‚  ancser-fever-cert-support-and-refactor-ancser-asyncapi [$!?] via đź¦€ v1.80\r\n.1\r\nâťŻ \r\n```",
